@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    The ShowPartUploads system door shows the users what files they have in
    the current conference's partupload directory.  It then gives them
    the option to delete or keep the file.

    When called during the login check it will scan all the conference
    partupload paths.  Not just the current conference.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The door is stored as:

    HBBS:Doors/System/ShowPartUploads/ShowPartUploads.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.10.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to a Commands/System file (HBBS:Commands/System is
    recommended).

    ShowPartUploads_Type_1=HBBS
    ShowPartUploads_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/ShowPartUploads/ShowPartUploads.HBBS {N} {O}

    If you want, you can let user's run this door by itself from the BBS prompt.
    Add the following lines to a Commands/#?Level#? file (HBBS:Commands/All_Levels is
    recommended).

    SPU_Type_1=HBBS
    SPU_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/ShowPartUploads/ShowPartUploads.HBBS {N}

    Note: Do not include the {O} in the line above when you're running it from
    the BBS prompt as the door accepts no user specified paramaters.

@EndNode

